ippine coastal forestry programs", "sort_order": 12}, {"name": "Camarines Sur Heritage Trees", "slug": "camarines-sur-heritage-trees", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Camarines Sur Province, Philippines - Eastern Luzon traditional groves", "traits": "Long-established landrace selections, proven genetic base", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Reliable monsoon-zone production", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 13}, {"name": "Canarium indicum (Galip Nut, Nangai Nut)", "slug": "canarium-indicum-galip-nut-nangai-nut", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Papua New Guinea, Solomon Islands, Vanuatu, Northern Australia", "traits": "Large tree 30m+, buttressed trunk 1m+ diameter, similar to pili", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR BOTH LOCATIONS: Native range includes Northern Australia - proven Australian adaptation. Tropical-subtropical tolerance. Related to pili but distinct species. Commercial cultivation in Pacific islands. May offer genetic diversity benefits if crossed with C. ovatum (research needed)", "availability": "Australian nurseries (northern regions); Pacific island nurseries; rare palm seed suppliers (rarepalmseeds.com)", "sort_order": 14}, {"name": "Canarium album (Chinese White Olive)", "slug": "canarium-album-chinese-white-olive", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "China - 2000+ year cultivation history", "traits": "Evergreen tree, tolerates light frost (MORE cold-hardy than pili). Subtropical-tropical range", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "BETTER FOR BRISBANE COLD TOLERANCE: Mature trees tolerate light frost vs. pili''s frost sensitivity. Ancient cultivation history. Medicinal properties (antioxidant, anti-inflammatory). Subtropical-adapted. May hybridize with pili for cold-hardy cultivars (research potential). Cultural significance in Chinese-Australian communities", "availability": "Chinese specialty nurseries; USDA-ARS germplasm (HCAN 2); limited Australian availability", "sort_order": 15}, {"name": "Canarium vulgare (Java Almond, Kenari)", "slug": "canarium-vulgare-java-almond-kenari", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Indonesia, Malaysia - Maritime Southeast Asia", "traits": "Similar to C. ovatum but distinct. Tropical lowland tree", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR KERALA: True tropical species. Perfect for monsoon climate. Commercial use in Indonesia. Processing traditions available. Cultural connection to Southeast Asian diaspora in Kerala", "availability": "Indonesian/Malaysian nurseries; regional seed networks; requires import certification", "sort_order": 16}, {"name": "Canarium luzonicum (Manila Elemi)", "slug": "canarium-luzonicum-manila-elemi", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Philippines (Quezon Province) - Indigenous", "traits": "Tall tree 35m, diameter 1m. Primarily grown for ELEMI RESIN (perfume, medicine)", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "DUAL-PURPOSE CROP: Elemi resin highly valuable (perfumery, aromatherapy, traditional medicine). Nuts edible but resin primary product. Indigenous Philippine species. Cultural significance. Potential alternative crop for Kerala''s spice/medicinal plant industry. Research collaboration opportunity", "availability": "Philippine forestry programs; indigenous resin collectors; limited cultivation - mostly wild harvest", "sort_order": 17}], "variety_count": 30}'::jsonb,
