nne-kew", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Venezuela (cultivated by Indigenous peoples), introduced from Cayenne, French Guiana 1820, to Queensland via Kew Gardens, England 1858 and 1881", "traits": "Large cylindrical fruit 2.5-3.0 kg, smooth leaves without spines, ovoid medium-sized, turns yellow from base to top when ripening", "flesh_fruit": "Pale-yellow to yellow, firm, close-textured, juicy, traditional pineapple flavor", "yield_notes": "Leading variety for canning, high yields, good fruit shape, 12-16° Brix, 0.5-1.0% acidity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Queen (Common Rough)", "slug": "queen-common-rough", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "South Africa and Australia (historic cultivation), widely distributed heritage variety", "traits": "Small to medium fruit 1-1.5 kg, dwarf compact plant, spiny dark purplish-green leaves, rough skin, conical shape, deeply placed eyes", "flesh_fruit": "Deep golden-yellow, crisp, less juicy than Cayenne but more aromatic, small core, tender, fine flavor", "yield_notes": "Lower than Cayenne, early maturity, produces 2+ suckers, 15-16° Brix, 0.6-0.8% acidity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Rough Leaf (Queen group)", "slug": "rough-leaf-queen-group", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Ripley Queen (Ripley)", "slug": "ripley-queen-ripley", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Queensland, Australia (developed in Queensland), 20th century selection", "traits": "Dwarf compact plant, crimson-tinged leaves, reddish-green leaves with brown spots, 3-6 pounds, golden rind when ripe, pale copper when fully mature, irregular bearer", "flesh_fruit": "Pale-yellow, non-fibrous, very sweet and rich, juicy, sweet-tart balance (13-15° Brix), low fiber", "yield_notes": "Takes 22 weeks from flowering to fruit maturity, 1.36-2.7 kg fruit", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "MacGregor (McGregor, Rough McGregor)", "slug": "macgregor-mcgregor-rough-mcgregor", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Queensland, Australia (hybridized from Smooth Cayenne in the 1980s), Australian creation", "traits": "Bright yellow rind, 4-7 pounds, square shoulders, larger fruit than typical Queen", "flesh_fruit": "Firm, sweet, low acidity, incredibly firm with more robust aroma than other Queen varieties", "yield_notes": "High productivity, disease resistant", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 7}, {"name": "Alexandra", "slug": "alexandra", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Queen variety selection, grown in Queensland and other regions", "traits": "Queen-type characteristics, moderate size", "flesh_fruit": "Golden-yellow, aromatic, sweet", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 8}, {"name": "James Queen", "slug": "james-queen", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "South Africa, also grown in Queensland", "traits": "Large size, dark green leaves with reddish spots", "flesh_fruit": "Reddish-orange flesh on exterior, yellow inside", "yield_notes": "Good", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 9}, {"name": "Queensland Cayenne", "slug": "queensland-cayenne", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Queensland, Australia (Queensland Department of Primary Industries), released 1975 after 20 years of breeding and testing", "traits": "Dual-purpose cultivar, specifically bred for Queensland conditions", "flesh_fruit": "Yellow, firm, suitable for both fresh market and canning", "yield_notes": "High, optimized for Queensland climate", "growing_notes": "Specifically developed for Brisbane/Queensland subtropical climate after two decades of research. Dual-purpose for fresh and processing. Represents Queensland''s commitment to pineapple breeding excellence. Well-adapted to local conditions.", "availability": "Queensland Department of Agriculture, heritage collections", "sort_order": 10}, {"name": "Hilo", "slug": "hilo", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Hawaii, USA (selected from Smooth Cayenne in Hilo region), 1960", "traits": "More compact plant than Smooth Cayenne, 3-5 pounds, softer rind, golden flesh", "flesh_fruit": "Golden, juicy, mildly sweet, slightly fibrous", "yield_notes": "Smaller, more cylindrical fruit, numerous suckers, no slips", "growing_notes": "Cayenne variant suitable for Brisbane. Less export-friendly due to softer rind but excellent tropical treat for local fresh markets. Thrives in zones 10-11 with volcanic soil and sun. Good for Brisbane''s subtropical climate.", "availability": "Specialty nurseries, tropical fruit collectors", "sort_order": 11}, {"name": "Sugarloaf (Kona Sugarloaf, White Sugarloaf, Brazilian White)", "slug": "sugarloaf-kona-sugarloaf-white-sugarloaf-brazilian-white", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "West Africa and Hawaii (also known as Pan de Azúcar in Spanish, Pain de Sucre in French), cultivated since 15th century sugar cone era", "traits": "Cylindrical conical shape resembling traditional sugarloaf, 5-6 pounds, green rind remains mostly green when ripe, smooth leaves, softer rind than most varieties", "flesh_fruit": "Creamy white to pale yellow, exceedingly sweet with hints of honey, almost no acidity (lowest acid pineapple), non-stringy, floral aroma, can reach 15° Brix, soft edible core (non-woody)", "yield_notes": "Moderate, 2-3 years to fruit", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 12}, {"name": "Red Spanish (Black Spanish, Large Key, Cuban)", "slug": "red-spanish-black-spanish-large-key-cuban", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Caribbean (possibly Hispaniola), spread across Central and South America by Spanish colonizers, historic variety", "traits": "Orange-red to deep red rind, smaller 2-5 pounds, squarish appearance, oval shape, tough skin excellent for shipping, spiny thorny leaves", "flesh_fruit": "Pale-yellow with hints of color, aromatic, fibrous, acidic and bold flavor, pleasant aroma, light yellow", "yield_notes": "1-2 kg, well-adapted for shipping as fresh fruit, moderate to high", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 13}, {"name": "Singapore Red", "slug": "singapore-red", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Malaysia/Singapore region, Spanish group", "traits": "Green leaves with reddish stripe at end, reddish cylindrical fruit, small size", "flesh_fruit": "Golden-yellow", "yield_notes": "Good, disease and pest-resistant", "growing_notes": "Disease and pest resistance makes it excellent for Brisbane''s humid climate. Great for canning. Subtropical adaptation.", "availability": "Specialty Asian variety nurseries, tropical fruit collectors", "sort_order": 14}, {"name": "Mauritius (Vazhakulam Pineapple, Kannara) 🏆", "slug": "mauritius-vazhakulam-pineapple-kannara", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 0}, {"name": "Kew (Giant Kew, Smooth Cayenne)", "slug": "kew-giant-kew-smooth-cayenne", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Venezuela (Indians), via Cayenne French Guiana 1820, introduced to India, known as Kew/Sarawak in India", "traits": "Large oblong 2-3 kg, slight taper towards crown, broad shallow eyes ideal for canning, yellow when fully ripe", "flesh_fruit": "Light yellow, juicy, fiberless, firm close-textured", "yield_notes": "High, late-maturing, most popular commercial variety in India, 12-14° Brix, 0.5-1.0% acidity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 1}, {"name": "Queen (Common Rough, Nanas Moris)", "slug": "queen-common-rough-nanas-moris", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Widely distributed heritage variety, also called Nanas Moris (Malaysia, from Mauritius name), leading cultivar Philippines, Queensland, South Africa", "traits": "Dwarf plant, short very spiny dark purplish-green leaves, compact, more cold and disease resistant, 1-2.5 pounds, petite, spiky leaves", "flesh_fruit": "Deep golden-yellow, tender, sweeter and more aromatic than Smooth Cayenne, small core, crispy, less juicy but higher quality flavor", "yield_notes": "Average 2 suckers or more for ratooning, 15-16° Brix, 0.6-0.8% acidity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 2}, {"name": "Jaldhup 🏆", "slug": "jaldhup", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Jaldhup region, India (named after place of maximum production), traditional Indian variety", "traits": "Falls under Queen group, smaller than Queen variety, local type", "flesh_fruit": "Well-balanced blend of sweetness with acidity, alcoholic flavor that can be differentiated from other Queen fruits", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "INDIGENOUS to India. Named after production region. Cultivated for both table and processing purposes. Perfectly adapted to Kerala''s tropical monsoon climate with distinctive local flavor profile. Grown in Meghalaya and Kerala. Unique alcoholic flavor note distinguishes it.", "availability": "Local Kerala markets, Jaldhup region growers, heritage collections", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Lakhat 🏆", "slug": "lakhat", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Lakhat region, India (named after place of maximum production), traditional Indian variety", "traits": "Falls under Queen group, smaller than Queen variety, local type", "flesh_fruit": "Sweet with balanced acidity", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "INDIGENOUS to India. Named after production region. Cultivated for both table and processing purposes. Well-adapted to Kerala monsoon conditions.", "availability": "Local Kerala markets, Lakhat region growers, Indian heritage collections", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "MD-2 (Del Monte Gold Extra Sweet, Dinar)", "slug": "md-2-del-monte-gold-extra-sweet-dinar", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Hawaii (Pineapple Research Institute), Costa Rica commercial production 1996, recommended for Kerala cultivation", "traits": "Cylindrical shape with square shoulders, amber skin, medium 1.5-2.0 kg, international market standard", "flesh_fruit": "Bright golden, very sweet, low acidity (0.4-0.45%), high Brix (17°), small core, resistant to internal browning", "yield_notes": "12-month plucking, high", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Abacaxi", "slug": "abacaxi", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Brazil (abacaxi is Brazilian Portuguese for pineapple), also Florida and Bahamas", "traits": "Tall, spiny, 2-11 pounds, bluish-green leaves with red-purple tinge, traditional appearance", "flesh_fruit": "Nearly translucent, white transparent, ultra-sweet, low acid, juicy, one of most delicious types", "yield_notes": "High, disease resistant", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "Pernambuco (Eleuthera)", "slug": "pernambuco-eleuthera", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Northeastern Brazil (Pernambuco state), also Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, Venezuela", "traits": "Vigorous plant, erect growth habit, semi-vigorous, long spiny leaves, oblong cylindrical shape, yellow-orange outside, 2-4 pounds, medium", "flesh_fruit": "Pale yellow to white, tender, juicy, mildly sweet, sweet melting, excellent flavor", "yield_notes": "1-2 kg, well-adapted to canning and processing, high sugar and acid content", "growing_notes": "Cultivation restricted to South American countries and suitable tropical regions. Excellent for eating fresh. Poorly adapted for shipping but perfect for local Kerala consumption. Disease resistance trait (used in Maspine hybrid breeding). Thrives in tropical monsoon conditions. Traditional fermented drink aluá made from scraps. Distinctive long spiny leaves. Zones 10-11 with sandy soil and summer blooms. From Brazil''s tropical coast.", "availability": "Specialty collectors, may be sourced from South American contacts for Kerala cultivation trials", "sort_order": 7}, {"name": "Sugarloaf (Pan de Azúcar, Kona)", "slug": "sugarloaf-pan-de-az-car-kona", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "West Africa, Hawaii, Puerto Rico, Philippines, South America, Cuba", "traits": "Cylindrical shape, tough rind but softer than other varieties, remains green even when ripe, 3-6 pounds", "flesh_fruit": "Juicy, creamy texture, white to pale yellow, floral aroma, sweet like honey, exceedingly sweet (up to 15° Brix), almost no acidity, edible non-woody core", "yield_notes": "Moderate, available year-round with peak mid-late summer", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 8}, {"name": "Red Spanish (Española Roja)", "slug": "red-spanish-espa-ola-roja", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Caribbean, Cuba, Venezuela, Mexico, West Indies, spread by Spanish colonizers", "traits": "Orange-red skin, 2-5 pounds, squarish, tough for shipping, spiny leaves", "flesh_fruit": "Pale yellow, light yellow with high fiber, aromatic, pleasant aroma, acidic bold flavor", "yield_notes": "1-2 kg, well-adapted for shipping and distant markets", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 9}, {"name": "Champaka (Champaka-153)", "slug": "champaka-champaka-153", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Cuba (studied in plantations in central Cuba), Spanish group", "traits": "Large plant, long dark green spiny sword-like leaves with reddish spots, medium to large fruit", "flesh_fruit": "Yellow to golden", "yield_notes": "Encouraging results in Cuban studies for production, disease resistance, and fruit weight", "growing_notes": "Currently studied in Cuba with encouraging results. Cuban tropical climate similar to Kerala monsoon conditions. Shows good production, disease resistance, and fruit weight. Could be excellent candidate for Kerala introduction from Cuban agricultural research.", "availability": "Cuban agricultural research stations, potential for Kerala cultivation trials", "sort_order": 10}, {"name": "Perola (Pearl)", "slug": "perola-pearl", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Brazil, studied in Cuba", "traits": "Brazilian variety with good characteristics", "flesh_fruit": "Sweet, good quality", "yield_notes": "Encouraging results in Cuban trials", "growing_notes": "Shows encouraging results in Cuban central plantation studies for production, disease resistance, and fruit weight. Brazilian origin suggests good tropical monsoon adaptation. Could be suitable for Kerala.", "availability": "Brazilian/Cuban sources, potential for Kerala cultivation", "sort_order": 11}, {"name": "Mordilona", "slug": "mordilona", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Northeastern Andes of Colombia and Venezuela, Mordilona group", "traits": "Large, irregular, cylindrical, yellow to orange peel", "flesh_fruit": "Cream-colored, sweet", "yield_notes": "Good", "growing_notes": "Cultivation restricted to certain South American countries. Genetic contributor to 73-50 hybrid (20% Mordilona). Tropical mountain origin suggests potential for Kerala highland areas. Sweet flesh good for fresh consumption.", "availability": "South American sources, specialty collectors", "sort_order": 12}, {"name": "Panare", "slug": "panare", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Venezuela (named after Panare Indian tribe who grew it), Bolivar State", "traits": "Medium-sized plant, long spiny leaves, bottle-shaped fruit, small 0.45-0.70 kg, small crown, ovate with deep eyes, orange externally", "flesh_fruit": "Deep yellow, slightly fragrant, little fiber, small core", "yield_notes": "Commercial cultivation to small extent", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 13}, {"name": "Maipure", "slug": "maipure", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Venezuela/South America", "traits": "Cylindrical, lighter skin, spiky leaves with red spots", "flesh_fruit": "Deep yellow", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 14}, {"name": "Montufar", "slug": "montufar", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Guatemala, Abacaxi group", "traits": "Conical shape, greenish rough rind, small to medium leaves with large border spikes", "flesh_fruit": "Beautiful bright yellow inside, yellowish-green outside", "yield_notes": "Great for juicing - creates tastiest pineapple juice", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 15}, {"name": "Brecheche", "slug": "brecheche", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Southern Venezuela (limited cultivation)", "traits": "Small size, medium olive-colored leaves, cylindrical shape, yellow color, spike-free plant", "flesh_fruit": "Very fragrant and juicy, little fiber, small core", "yield_notes": "Limited but excellent quality", "growing_notes": "Spike-free advantage for handling and cultivation. Very fragrant with little fiber makes it premium quality. Venezuelan tropical origin suits Kerala climate. Small cylinder shape distinctive.", "availability": "Venezuelan specialty sources, rare collector variety", "sort_order": 16}, {"name": "Santa Marta (Santa Marta No. 1)", "slug": "santa-marta-santa-marta-no-1", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Colombia (Cayenne strain)", "traits": "Subject to cracking of core in hot dry weather", "flesh_fruit": "Good quality when conditions suitable", "yield_notes": "Moderate, weather-dependent", "growing_notes": "Colombian Cayenne strain. Issue with core cracking in hot/dry weather less problematic in Kerala''s humid monsoon climate with ample rainfall. Worth testing in Kerala conditions.", "availability": "Colombian agricultural sources, research collections", "sort_order": 17}, {"name": "Cayena Lisa", "slug": "cayena-lisa", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Spanish name for Smooth Cayenne, widely grown in Spanish-speaking regions", "traits": "Long wide leaves, cylindrical fruit, few spikes at top of leaves", "flesh_fruit": "Reddish orange outside, pale-yellow inside", "yield_notes": "Good", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 18}, {"name": "PR-1-67 (Roja Española type)", "slug": "pr-1-67-roja-espa-ola-type", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Puerto Rico (similar to Roja Española)", "traits": "Barrel-shaped, yellow-orange exterior, yellowish-green leaves with reddish tinge", "flesh_fruit": "Good quality", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "Puerto Rican selection of Red Spanish type. Puerto Rico''s tropical monsoon climate very similar to Kerala. Proven tropical adaptation.", "availability": "Puerto Rican agricultural sources, Caribbean connections", "sort_order": 19}, {"name": "Spanish Jewel", "slug": "spanish-jewel", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Spanish group selection", "traits": "Cylindrical shape, rectangular flat deep eyes, wide long dark green leaves, white outside", "flesh_fruit": "Orange inside", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 20}, {"name": "Sarawak (Nanas Moris - Peninsular Malaysia)", "slug": "sarawak-nanas-moris-peninsular-malaysia", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Malaysia (Peninsular Malaysia), also known in India/Sri Lanka/Thailand as Sarawak/Kew", "traits": "Vigorous growing, large about 2.5 kg, egg-shaped fruit on short strong peduncle, broad flat fruitlets/eyes", "flesh_fruit": "Yellow, good quality", "yield_notes": "High, leading cultivar Taiwan", "growing_notes": "Malaysian tropical climate very similar to Kerala monsoon. Already known in India as Kew/Sarawak. Vigorous growth suits Kerala''s humid conditions. Does not respond readily to flower induction on peat but excellent on mineral soil.", "availability": "Malaysian sources, already present in India as Kew variety, Southeast Asian connections", "sort_order": 21}, {"name": "Maspine (Line 73-50)", "slug": "maspine-line-73-50", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Malaysia (MARDI Station, Pontian, Johore), released May 5, 2005 after 10 years research (1993-2004)", "traits": "Manzanah group, medium-sized crown, seldom has stem, aerial and ground shoots, ≥80% flowering response", "flesh_fruit": "Golden yellow, high sugar content", "yield_notes": "High yielding, productive, red-heart inflorescence 37 days after hormone treatment", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 22}, {"name": "Phuket (Queen type)", "slug": "phuket-queen-type", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Thailand (Phuket region), Queen variety", "traits": "Queen characteristics, smaller size", "flesh_fruit": "Golden-yellow, aromatic, sweet", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 23}, {"name": "Victoria (Queen type)", "slug": "victoria-queen-type", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Queen variety, various tropical regions", "traits": "Queen group characteristics, compact", "flesh_fruit": "Golden, sweet, aromatic", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 24}], "variety_count": 40}'::jsonb,
