 "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 2}, {"name": "Lost Hills", "slug": "lost-hills", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "University of California breeding program (released 2005, sister variety to Golden Hills with same parentage)", "traits": "Similar to Kerman in canopy shape and growth pattern (unlike Golden Hills'' upright habit), early flowering and harvest (1-2 weeks before Kerman), less alternate bearing tendency than Kerman or Golden Hills, more consistent year-to-year production", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Higher yields in first 5 years compared to Kerman, produces more consistently across years, reduces feast/famine cycle of alternate bearing", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Gumdrop", "slug": "gumdrop", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "University of California breeding program (released 2016, newest commercial variety)", "traits": "EXTRA-EARLY harvest (10-12 days before Golden Hills, 24 days before Kerman), fastest growth rate of all varieties, thicker trunk requiring larger diameter rootstock, sticky ''gummy'' husk (variety name origin), vigorous and fast-growing", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good yield potential comparable to other modern varieties, still establishing long-term production data as trees mature", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Red Aleppo (Ashouri) 🏆", "slug": "red-aleppo-ashouri", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Aleppo, Syria (ancient variety, cultivated for centuries in Syria and Levant region)", "traits": "Medium-sized tree, distinctive red outer husk that gives variety its name, medium-sized nuts, good productivity, adapted to Syrian semi-desert climate", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good productivity, reliable in appropriate climate", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 5}, {"name"