n", "flesh_fruit": "Not ideal for eating, grown primarily for size", "yield_notes": "Usually 1 pumpkin per plant when grown for size", "growing_notes": "Struggles in tropical climates but can be attempted in Brisbane with care. Best in cooler regions. Requires extensive space. Descended from French Jaune Gros de Paris.", "availability": "Diggers Club, specialty competition pumpkin suppliers", "sort_order": 18}, {"name": "Silver Edge (Cushaw)", "slug": "silver-edge-cushaw", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Native American heirloom", "traits": "Round or pear-shaped, white with mottled green stripes", "flesh_fruit": "Good eating, but primarily grown for large tasty silver-edged seeds", "yield_notes": "Good seed production", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 19}, {"name": "Kumi Kumi (Kamo Kamo)", "slug": "kumi-kumi-kamo-kamo", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "New Zealand (Maori heirloom)", "traits": "Heavily ribbed, speckled green, soft skin, 20-30cm across", "flesh_fruit": "Pale, excellent flavor when young", "yield_notes": "Good production", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 20}, {"name": "Small Sugar (New England Pie)", "slug": "small-sugar-new-england-pie", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "United States (pre-1860)", "traits": "Small (2-3kg, 20cm across), deep orange, round", "flesh_fruit": "Sweet, fine-grained, deep orange, excellent for pies", "yield_notes": "Good production", "growing_notes": "Traditional pie pumpkin. Grows in Brisbane. Stores well. Classic American heirloom.", "availability": "The Lost Seed, Happy Valley Seeds, Southern Harvest", "sort_order": 21}, {"name": "Big Max", "slug": "big-max", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "United States", "traits": "Large, round, bright orange, can grow massive under ideal conditions", "flesh_fruit":